<subSubSection pageId="56" pageNumber="185" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="56.[1373,2583,1123,2023]" pageId="56" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1374,2076,1714,1747]" pageId="56" pageNumber="185">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
The three known specimens of the Narrow-headed Slender Opossum were trapped on the ground, but little is known about its social behavior.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="56" pageNumber="185" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="56.[1373,2583,1123,2023]" pageId="56" pageNumber="185">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1375,1727,1832,1865]" pageId="56" pageNumber="185">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The Narrow-headed Slender Opossum is known from only three specimens from a single locality. There are no new recordssince it was described in 1979, and existing information is insufficient to assess any conservation status.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
